  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Why Specialized Business English Matters</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">General English courses often focus on daily life, like ordering food or asking for directions. Business English is different. It is about negotiation, presentation skills, email etiquette, and industry-specific vocabulary. A general tutor might not understand the nuances of a corporate board meeting or a technical sales pitch. That is why choosing a platform with specialized business tracks is essential for professionals.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">In 2026, the global economy is more connected than ever. Whether you are a developer in Brazil working for a US startup or a marketing manager in Japan coordinating with a team in Germany, English is the bridge. However, "broken English" is often not enough to build trust in high-stakes environments. Professional tutors help you move beyond being "understood" to being "persuasive."</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-16 mb-6">1. Preply: The Professional Choice</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Preply has positioned itself as a leader in the professional learning space. Their "Preply Business" wing provides companies with a way to train entire teams, but individual learners benefit from the same high standards. The platform uses an advanced matching algorithm to connect you with tutors who have backgrounds in finance, tech, law, or marketing.</p>
  
  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Key Features for Professionals</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
    <li>Industry-specific filters (e.g., "English for IT" or "Medical English")</li>
    <li>Structured learning plans focused on workplace goals</li>
    <li>Integrated virtual classroom with screen sharing and note-taking</li>
    <li>Progress tracking reports to show your improvement over time</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">The real strength of Preply lies in its search filters. You can search for tutors who specifically mention "Interview Preparation" or "Business Writing." Many of these tutors are not just English teachers; they are former business professionals themselves. This means they can give you feedback on your actual presentation slides or help you prepare for a specific industry event.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-16 mb-6">2. iTalki: The Expert Marketplace</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">While iTalki is known for its massive variety, it is also home to some of the most experienced professional teachers in the world. Many tutors on iTalki are former corporate executives or certified business trainers who have moved to freelance teaching. The marketplace model allows you to find high-level expertise without the high-level price tag of a traditional language school.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Why it Works for Business</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
    <li>Direct access to "Professional Teachers" with verified credentials</li>
    <li>Flexible scheduling that fits around a busy work week</li>
    <li>Opportunity to find tutors with specific regional business experience</li>
    <li>Pay-per-lesson model means no long-term financial commitment</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">On iTalki, you are in the driver's seat. You can browse through thousands of video introductions to find a tutor whose accent and teaching style match your needs. For business learners, this is crucial. If you are going to be working with a team in London, you might want to find a tutor from the UK to help you get used to the accent and British business culture.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-16 mb-6">3. Cambly Business: Total Flexibility</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Cambly Business is designed for the modern professional who never knows when their next free 15 minutes will be. Unlike other platforms that require booking hours in advance, Cambly allows you to jump on a call whenever you have a break. Their business curriculum covers essential topics like "Conducting a Meeting" and "Giving a Presentation."</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">The Cambly Advantage</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
    <li>Instant 24/7 access to native speakers</li>
    <li>Curated business courses included in the subscription</li>
    <li>Mobile app allows for practice during commutes or travel</li>
    <li>Focus on conversational fluency and "sounding natural" in office settings</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">The convenience of Cambly is hard to beat. If you have a sudden meeting in English and want to warm up your voice, you can connect to a tutor in seconds. While it might lack the deep academic structure of Preply, it is excellent for building the confidence needed to speak up in a group setting.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-16 mb-6">4. Lingoda: Structured Group Learning</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">If you prefer a more traditional classroom feel but with the convenience of online learning, Lingoda is a fantastic option. They offer a specific "Business English" track that follows the CEFR levels (A1 to C1). Lessons are taught in small groups, which is great for practicing how to interact with multiple people—a common requirement in corporate life.</p>
  
  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">The Lingoda Experience</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
    <li>CEFR-aligned curriculum with downloadable materials</li>
    <li>Small group classes (max 5 students) for realistic interaction</li>
    <li>The "Sprint" challenges can help you make rapid progress</li>
    <li>Certificates that you can add to your LinkedIn profile</li>
  </ul>

